  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "ecbffa19-6de5-446d-b303-b2eb5231dbdd",
    "name": "ItsaCheckmate Marketplace for Developers API",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": {
      "content": "ItsaCheckmate (Checkmate) is restaurant middleware that connects point-of-sale (POS) systems to delivery marketplaces and online ordering channels. The Marketplace for Developers API is an open REST API that lets technology partners build a single integration to read and write menus, orders, and locations across 50+ POS systems and 100+ ordering platforms.\nAuthentication uses an OAuth-style flow: a token endpoint issues short-lived, scoped access tokens (24-hour default expiry) and refresh tokens. After obtaining a token a partner must call the Activate Location endpoint before any menu or order operation will succeed. Menu retrieval requires the `menus` scope. Order submission supports both standard and group orders via a `group_order` flag and requires a verified location.\nEndpoints documented here were confirmed from the official Checkmate developer reference (openapi-itsacheckmate.readme.io) and its llms.txt index. The reference also publishes ready-to-use Postman collections and an Update Notice webhook for real-time menu synchronization.\n\nContact Support:\n Name: ItsaCheckmate Marketplace for Developers",
      "type": "text/plain"
    }
  }
}